==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[jungere]]'': join through {{OF.}} ''[[joindre]]'': to join

===Adjective===
'''joinder'''

# {{law}} The [[join]]ing  a [[litigant]] to a [[suit]].

====Usage notes====
A litigant is joined by a  "notice of joinder". The substantive application is an "application for joinder"

